  note = {Lunar small satellite;Spacecraft structures;},
  abstract = {Part of the Stuttgart Small Satellite Program at the Institute of
	Space Systems of the Universita&die;t Stuttgart, Lunar Mission BW1
	is a lunar small satellite powered by an electric propulsion system.
	As a first step within this paper, the specification of a satellite
	structure for the Lunar Mission BW1 is compiled and sub-functions
	are being derived. Suitable solutions for the sub-functions are combined,
	to generate first structure concepts. After identifying all prospective
	systems, which are planned to be Integrated in the probe, the four
	most promising structure configurations are built as CAD and FEM
	models, to carry out assembly analyses and gain information about
	their stiffness and mass. Ensuing, all structure variants are evaluated
	with the aid of a target value analysis. At the moment the two most
	promising structure concepts are being enhanced to get more detailed
	Information on their mechanical properties to reduce their weight.
	This paper will show the results of the concept study for the Lunar
	Mission BW1 as well as the ongoing activities. It presents a systematic
	method for the development of satellite structures and shows first
	results of a possible spacecraft structure for the Lunar Mission
